                                <div class="tabing-contant">
                                    <p>Council for International Organizations of Medical Sciences (CIOMS), defines a
                                        safety signal as "information that arises from one or multiple sources
                                        (including observations or experiments), which suggests a new, potentially
                                        causal association, or a new aspect of a known association between an
                                        intervention [e.g., administration of a medicine] and an event or set of related
                                        events, either adverse or beneficial, that is judged to be of sufficient
                                        likelihood to justify verificatory action."</p>
